(:summary    "Log keyboard commands to buffer"
 :created    "2004"
 :updated    "20041106"
 :license    "GPL-2"
 :authors    (("Michael Weber" . "michaelw@foldr.org"))
 :maintainer ("Michael Weber" . "michaelw@foldr.org")
 :provided   (mwe-log-commands)
 :required   ((("emacs" cl)))
 :keywords   ("help")
 :homepage   "http://www.foldr.org/~michaelw/emacs/"
 :wikipage   "http://www.emacswiki.org/CommandLogMode"
 :commentary "\
This add-on can be used to demo Emacs to an audience.  When
activated, keystrokes get logged into a designated buffer, along
with the command bound to them.

To enable, use e.g.: 

(add-hook 'LaTeX-mode-hook (function mwe:log-keyboard-commands))

To see the log buffer, call M-x mwe:open-command-log-buffer.")
